examples.en: My health has been materially worse.
She was never without reading material.
This would materially affect US security.
Materially, we are better off than ever before.
It aided him materially in winning the argument.
What is formally correct may be materially false.
The curtains required yards of expensive material.
He is concerned only with his own material comforts.
The researchers included all data that was material.
They made some short cuts, by which the road was materially shortened.
A gigantic raise in freight rates would have added materially to the inflation.
